      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-problem&#34;&gt;The problem&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When you need to get remote files to handle its content (i.e. csv files) you may find out that accesing them isn&amp;rsquo;t as easy as using fopen:
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34; style=&#34;background: #272822&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;line-height: 125%&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color: #75715e&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;?php&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color: #f8f8f2&#34;&gt;$handle&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color: #f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color: #f8f8f2&#34;&gt;fopen($filename,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color: #e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;quot;r&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color: #f8f8f2&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color: #66d9ef&#34;&gt;or&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color: #66d9ef&#34;&gt;die&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color: #f8f8f2&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color: #e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;could not open .&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color: #f8f8f2&#34;&gt;$filename);&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

